<br>
As for where to go looking for this, there are a few places.  PoP zones like PoI can drop decent sleeves.  Also, the PoP dark pages quest results in a good cloak (definatly check this one out).  For belt, if you have the cash or want to hunt it, silverflank from CT is a good one; there are others with decent stats as well (check the baz).  Legs offers a few choices such as black-something (forget name, check baz), or the ones from SD.  Boots .. well anything beats ac1 off jboots, try the sandles from SD or the quested earthen boots (can get in an hour) if you just want any stats .. if you want actual good ones try the shrouded boots from ME, which are easy to get.<br>
<br>
For hunting zones... Well SS is definatly worth it if you can get regular ToV raids.  May take a few raids, but going from any of those items to SS is a big jump for you.  Most of them are kinda hard to upgrade as well, meaning they will last awhile.  Umbral is an ok zone, with the dreamweaver gear set being uncommon-ish with decent stats for some slots.  PoI and ME have a drop or two you could use, like the sleeves or boots.  You could try CT for belt and boots, but at 58 it may be too rough.<br>
<br>
Also most of those slots have upgrades in the few k range (like 2 to 8 or so).  PotC ear, Silverflank belt, dreamweaver webshield, are all things that come to mind.  Checking the baz for a week to get an idea and seeing how much pp you have to throw at it could be a good idea.<br>
<br>
Also of note, finishing shawl 8 is a good idea that will help out.  Also that quest cloak I mentioned form PoK would be a great addition.  Work on those two things while you hunt for sure. <p><!--EZCODE HR START--><hr /><!--EZCODE HR END--><br>
